\"https://github.com/grammarly/rocker-compose\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">410</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":410,\"repo\":\"grammarly/rocker-compose\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> 💀 - Docker composition tool with idempotency features for deploying apps composed of multiple containers. By<a href=\"https://github.com/veggiemonk/awesome-docker/blob/master/grammarly\">@grammarly</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:49:31.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"veggiemonk/awesome-docker","categoryHTML":"<h2>Container Operations</h2><h3>Container Composition</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/grammarly/rocker\">rocker</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/grammarly/rocker\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1335,\"repo\":\"grammarly/rocker\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> 💀 - Extended Dockerfile builder. Supports multiple FROMs, MOUNTS, templates, etc. by <a href=\"https://github.com/veggiemonk/awesome-docker/blob/master/grammarly\">@grammarly</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:49:31.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"rust-unofficial/awesome-rust","categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Network programming</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>NATS\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nats-io/nats.rs\">nats-io/nats.rs</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/nats-io/nats.rs\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">304</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":304,\"repo\":\"nats-io/nats.rs\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> — Rust client for NATS, the cloud native messaging system. <a href=\"https://github.com/nats-io/nats.rs/actions\"><img src=\"https://github.com/nats-io/nats.rs/workflows/Rust/badge.svg?branch=master\" alt=\"Build Status\"></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:38:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mourarthur/awesome-credit-modeling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Credit Scoring</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1007/s10462-015-9434-x\">Financial credit risk assessment: a recent review</a> - Summarizes the traditional statistical models and state-of-the-art intelligent methods for financial distress forecasting, with emphasis on the most recent achievements.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mourarthur/awesome-credit-modeling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Credit Scoring</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1057/jors.2012.145\">A literature review on the application of evolutionary computing to credit scoring</a> - The aim of this paper is to summarize the most recent developments in the application of evolutionary algorithms to credit scoring by means of a thorough review of scientific articles published during the period 2000–2012.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mourarthur/awesome-credit-modeling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Credit Scoring</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://alo.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Household-behaviorConsumer-credit-riskCredit-card-borrowingMachine-learningNonparametric-estimation.pdf\">Consumer credit-risk models via machine-learning algorithms</a> - The authors apply machine-learning techniques to construct nonlinear nonparametric forecasting models of consumer credit risk. They are able to construct out-of-sample forecasts that signiﬁcantly improve the classiﬁcation rates of credit-card-holder delinquencies and defaults.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mourarthur/awesome-credit-modeling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Credit Scoring</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/7033125\">Example-Dependent Cost-Sensitive Logistic Regression for Credit Scoring</a> - Several real-world classification problems are example-dependent cost-sensitive in nature, where the costs due to misclassification vary between examples. Credit scoring is a typical example of cost-sensitive classification. However, it is usually treated using methods that do not take into account the real financial costs associated with the lending business.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mourarthur/awesome-credit-modeling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Credit Scoring</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0957417416306947\">A comparative study on base classifiers in ensemble methods for credit scoring</a> - In the last years, the application of artificial intelligence methods on credit risk assessment has meant an improvement over classic methods. Recent works show that ensembles of classifiers achieve the better results for this kind of tasks.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mourarthur/awesome-credit-modeling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Credit Scoring</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0169207000000340\">A survey of credit and behavioural scoring: forecasting financial risk of lending to consumers</a> - Surveys the techniques used — both statistical and operational research based — to help organisations decide whether or not to grant credit to consumers. It also discusses the need to incorporate economic conditions into the scoring systems and the way the systems could change from estimating the probability of a consumer defaulting to estimating the profit a consumer will bring to the lending organisation.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mourarthur/awesome-credit-modeling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Credit Scoring</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0957417407006719\">The comparisons of data mining techniques for the predictive accuracy of probability of default of credit card clients</a> - This research compares the predictive accuracy of probability of default among six data mining methods. From the perspective of risk management, the result of predictive accuracy of the estimated probability of default will be more valuable than the binary result of classification.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mourarthur/awesome-credit-modeling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Credit Scoring</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2005.14658\">Super-App Behavioral Patterns in Credit Risk Models: Financial, Statistical and Regulatory Implications</a> - Presents the impact of alternative data that originates from an app-based marketplace, in contrast to traditional bureau data, upon credit scoring models. These alternative data sources have shown themselves to be immensely powerful in predicting borrower behavior in segments traditionally underserved by banks and financial institutions. At the same time alternative data must be carefully validated to overcome regulatory hurdles across diverse jurisdictions.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mourarthur/awesome-credit-modeling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Institutional Credit Risk</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11009-008-9078-2\">Random Survival Forests Models for SME Credit Risk Measurement</a> - Extends the existing literature on empirical research in the field of credit risk default for Small Medium Enterprizes (SMEs), proposing a non-parametric approach based on Random Survival Forests (RSF) and comparing its performance with a standard logit model.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mourarthur/awesome-credit-modeling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Institutional Credit Risk</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2004.08204\">Modeling Institutional Credit Risk with Financial News</a> - Current work in downgrade risk modeling depends on multiple variations of quantitative measures provided by third-party rating agencies and risk management consultancy companies. There has been a wide push into using alternative sources of data, such as financial news, earnings call transcripts, or social media content, to possibly gain a competitive edge in the industry. This paper proposes a predictive downgrade model using solely news data represented by neural network embeddings.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mourarthur/awesome-credit-modeling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Institutional Credit Risk</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/935101\">Bankruptcy prediction for credit risk using neural networks: A survey and new results</a> - The prediction of corporate bankruptcies is an important and widely studied topic since it can have significant impact on bank lending decisions and profitability. This work reviews the topic of bankruptcy prediction, with emphasis on neural-network (NN) models and develops an NN bankruptcy prediction model, proposing novel indicators for the NN system.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mourarthur/awesome-credit-modeling","categoryHTML":"<h2>Model Explainability</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.bankofengland.co.uk/working-paper/2019/machine-learning-explainability-in-finance-an-application-to-default-risk-analysis\">Machine learning explainability in finance: an application to default risk analysis</a> - This Staff Working Paper from the Bank of England proposes a framework for addressing the ‘black box’ problem present in some Machine Learning (ML) applications.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"rust-unofficial/awesome-rust","categoryHTML":"<h2>Development tools</h2><h3>Services</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/deps-rs/deps.rs\">deps.rs</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/deps-rs/deps.rs\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">255</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":255,\"repo\":\"deps-rs/deps.rs\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> — Detect outdated or insecure dependencies</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-28T19:29:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"agamm/awesome-developer-first","categoryHTML":"<h2>Discussions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a hr